HEADWORD: Nitranilic
<hw>Ni`tra*nil"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Nitro-</ets> + chlor<ets>anil</ets> + <ets>-ic</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>Of, pertaining to, or designating, a complex
organic acid produced as a white crystalline substance by the action of
